Center: US National Nuclear Data Center, Brookhaven, USA
title: Spallation of Aluminum by 28-GeV Protons

x4codes.hlp: Brookhaven National Laboratory, Upton, NY, United States of America
Brookhaven National Laboratory, Upton, NY, United States of America

x4freetext: Stacks of aluminum and polyethylene or
polystyrene foils were irradiated in the internal
beam of the Brookhaven alternating gradient
synchrotron at an energy of 28 GeV.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The errors on the individual values have
been compounded from the errors due to counting
statistics (negligible for Na24 and F18) and a 1.5%
error to allow for uncertainties in weighing and foil
line-up and for small day-to-day variations of the
counter efficiencies from the calibrated values.
Errors include estimates of systematic effects but do
not include the 4.6% error in the C12(p,pn)C11 cross
